A RESOLUTION
1 Recognizing February 11, 2025, as Sex Trafficking Awareness Day at the state capitol; and
2 for other purposes.
3 WHEREAS, sex trafficking is a form of modern day slavery wherein people profit from the
4 control and exploitation of others and is a horrific crime perpetrated against women and
5 children; and
6 WHEREAS, in 2023, the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children received more
7 than 18,400 reports of possible child sex trafficking; and
8 WHEREAS, the National Center for Missing and Exploited Children estimates that 1 in 6
9 of the more than 28,800 cases of children reported missing in 2023 were likely victims of
10 child sex trafficking; and
11 WHEREAS, the latest numbers from the United States National Human Trafficking Hotline
12 indicate that 10,359 situations of human trafficking were reported in a year, involving 16,554
13 individual victims; and
