14 WHEREAS, Georgia ranks second in number of calls to the National Human Trafficking
15 Hotline per capita, which shows that efforts to educate the public on signs of trafficking are
16 successful and should be ongoing; and
17 WHEREAS, the average age of entry into commercial sexual exploitation for minors served
18 by Street Grace in Georgia is 14 years old; and
19 WHEREAS, Street Grace has served minor sex trafficking victims from 80 counties in
20 Georgia; and
21 WHEREAS, Street Grace has provided services to more than 5,600 exploited individuals;
22 and
23 WHEREAS, grassroots activists will gather at the state capitol on February 11, 2025, to raise
24 awareness about the need to end sex trafficking in Georgia; and
25 WHEREAS, Street Grace has worked to organize and empower tens of thousands of
26 grassroots activists across the State of Georgia to end sex trafficking.
27 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES that
28 the members of this body recognize February 11, 2025, as Sex Trafficking Awareness Day
29 at the state capitol.
30 BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED that the Clerk of the House of Representatives is authorized
31 and directed to make an appropriate copy of this resolution available for distribution to Street
32 Grace.
